Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.33,0:00:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, there! It's time for Kaleido Star!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.23,0:00:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When you watch Kaleido Star, please \Nkeep your room brightly lit,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.87,0:00:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and sit as far from the TV as you can.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.58,0:00:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, well, well. Does everyone \Nlike amusement parks?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.71,0:00:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Merry-go-rounds and roller coasters!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.83,0:00:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They thrill you and make \Nyour heart skip a beat.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.80,0:00:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're fun, aren't they? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.05,0:00:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our show is performed in a different \Nspace from a regular stage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.08,0:00:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order for everyone to enjoy our show, \Nwe will give it everything we've got!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.12,0:00:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dare mo sagashiteru yume wa kitto aru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.02,0:00:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dokoka ni aru {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:01:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Negai ga itsuka kanau made hitori ja nai{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.25,0:01:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Saigo made yareru to ittetane {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kitto tsuyogatte itanda {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Itsudatte muchabakka de zutto karamawari de{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.56,0:01:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dakedo anata dake ga soba ni ita{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.95,0:01:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Daremo sagashiteru yume wa kitto aru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.91,0:01:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Arukidaseru {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Koko kara nanika ga hajimaru {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.13,0:01:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shinjite itai {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.17,0:02:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mada minu hikari yakusoku \Nno basho e to tsuzuite yuku{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.68,0:02:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Negai ga itsuka kanau made hitori ja naisa{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.13,0:02:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who? Who's that?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.67,0:02:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She's amazing. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.04,0:02:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She nailed everyone's \Nattention in an instant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.45,0:02:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's only one who's capable \Nof doing something like this...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.62,0:02:59.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"The Amazing Mystery Star."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.45,0:03:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So under these conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.79,0:03:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to make a contract \Nwith all members of Freedom Lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.66,0:03:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got a job! We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.48,0:03:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking forward to working for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.70,0:03:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially on that Masked Star.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.59,0:03:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.96,0:03:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That masked...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she is really incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.70,0:03:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you say if I suggest that you \Ndrastically increase the Masked Star's time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.22,0:03:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... that Masked Star is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.04,0:03:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will definitely consider \Nwhat you just said.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.81,0:03:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.50,0:03:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do, \Nsaying something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.08,0:03:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know who that Masked Star is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.62,0:03:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to patch things up for \Nthe moment by using a substitute?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.97,0:03:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.50,0:03:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.47,0:03:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause I know the identity of \Nthat Masked Star is Miss Layla.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.75,0:03:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla is not here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:03:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Then do you know about \Nwhat time she'll be home?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.22,0:04:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She left here for Europe about \Na week ago for a movie shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.04,0:04:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Europe?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.66,0:04:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there some kind of mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Excuse me, but I have to go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.02,0:04:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot believe this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.46,0:04:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that Masked Star is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.83,0:04:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As we were saying, we have \Nto use a substitute tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.01,0:04:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.29,0:04:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since {\i1}someone {\i0}caused all this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.87,0:04:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we have to ask her to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.99,0:04:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, wear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.88,0:04:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tada!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.41,0:04:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was worth staying up all night making it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.79,0:04:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the difference in height is way too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.70,0:04:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought. So I brought these.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.37,0:04:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wear something like that and perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.95,0:04:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let's try to contact \NMiss Layla one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.20,0:04:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going over there is ten hours one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.00,0:04:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible, Sora.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.83,0:04:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um.... Then why don't we tell \Nthe Park Owner the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:05:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That the Masked Star is not \Na member of Freedom Lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.04,0:05:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're going to risk losing \Nthe contract by doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.50,0:05:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen... Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.31,0:05:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.00,0:05:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rosetta.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the Masked Star here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.90,0:05:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She looks different, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... No... It's not her. Rosetta, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.77,0:05:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rosetta, tell them there's no way I \Ncan substitute for the Masked Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.62,0:05:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora is going to substitute \Nfor the Masked Star?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.96,0:05:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I never realized that \Nwe can use that trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.13,0:05:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, look at today's newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? This is about yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.50,0:05:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The amusement park where I \Nwent with my family by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.50,0:05:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, they were performing a wonderful show
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as good as anything you'd see in Las Vegas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.07,0:05:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The performance of the Masked \NStar who appeared for the finale
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was especially bold and elegant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.62,0:05:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I thought I was able to see a show \Nlike that just for the price of admission,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.01,0:06:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it really moved me."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.29,0:06:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.45,0:06:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of this article, \Nwe may have more customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.82,0:06:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible! It was just yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.26,0:06:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have plenty of time until \Nthe Masked Star's show starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.83,0:06:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't push. Please \Nenter slowly in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.54,0:06:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All these people came to see the Masked Star?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.16,0:06:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now what are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.45,0:06:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know you were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, this is the biggest crowd \Nwe've ever had since we opened this park.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Owner...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all thanks to that \NMasked Star right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.83,0:06:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.87,0:06:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're also glad we could help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.58,0:06:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's also what this Masked Star is saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.00,0:06:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm? I don't know why, but doesn't \Nshe look different from yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.82,0:06:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.04,0:06:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... I wonder if it's my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.29,0:07:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, anyway, we also \Nhave a TV reporter today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So make sure to give us a nice show.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A TV reporter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.20,0:07:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resign yourself to it, Sora.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.62,0:07:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A flying jellyfish girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.79,0:07:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go! Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.65,0:07:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.11,0:07:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Masked Star is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.45,0:07:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy, where's the Masked Star?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it about the time she shows up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.75,0:07:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:07:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it time yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.75,0:08:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.91,0:08:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Masked Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.91,0:08:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Close-up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.66,0:08:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.62,0:08:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.83,0:08:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something is... different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.70,0:08:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.35,0:08:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I wish the real one would show up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masked Star! Masked Star! Masked \NStar! Masked Star! Masked Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.14,0:08:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masked Star! Masked Star! Masked \NStar! Masked Star! Masked Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.75,0:08:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice but to just do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.00,0:08:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just do it! Just do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch! Ouch! Huh? Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.91,0:09:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.24,0:09:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disappointed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.40,0:09:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a waste of time to \Ncome all the way down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.39,0:09:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking forward to your next visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.12,0:09:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real Masked Star will \Nappear for sure tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.09,0:09:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're telling me the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.84,0:09:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So tomorrow, she will be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.58,0:09:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please make sure to advertise our park.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.37,0:09:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.67,0:09:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have you doing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.58,0:09:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, to tell you the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to hear your excuses!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.06,0:09:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the Masked Star doesn't show up tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to cancel the contract!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.45,0:09:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're going to pay for the forfeit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.55,0:09:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Capisci{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.29,0:09:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come up with any good ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.01,0:09:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.87,0:09:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.88,0:09:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Masked Star is Miss \NLayla. Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what you were thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.56,0:09:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never realized you were so tenacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.65,0:10:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you think, it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.87,0:10:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who else could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.77,0:10:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't guess who she is, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}'Cause Miss Layla... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.88,0:10:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Kaleido Stage closes its door, \Nit cannot close the door to my future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.58,0:10:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will not be my last \Nshow, unless I wish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.42,0:10:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think that's the way \NMiss Layla really feels.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.50,0:10:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I have time \Nfor anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.85,0:10:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, my father is \Nmanaging my schedule right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.46,0:10:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At that time, Miss Layla looked like she \Nwas forcing herself to act that way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.50,0:10:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's why I thought she came \Nback as the Masked Star.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I wonder if I'm wrong \Nlike everybody else says.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.83,0:10:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, I'm afraid we \Nhave to use the last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What last resort?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.85,0:10:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to make the show get canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:10:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to pray for rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:11:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain, Rain. Please rain. Please rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain, Rain. Please rain. Please rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.39,0:11:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain, rain. Rain, rain, rain. \NDrop rain. Drop rain. Drop rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.60,0:11:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Katsu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.70,0:11:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a nice day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we get a clear day, \Nthere's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.79,0:11:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, pull yourself together, and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.96,0:11:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're worried about the \Nforfeit, you don't need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.45,0:11:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not an amount we can pay easily anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.52,0:11:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you come to terms with the fact that \Nyou'll be paying it back the rest of your lives
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.70,0:11:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it'll be no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.04,0:11:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... You're not encouraging at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.72,0:11:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.03,0:11:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good morning Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.24,0:11:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't they look wobbly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.66,0:12:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. They're just a little depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.83,0:12:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.83,0:12:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what's wrong with \Nthe current Kaleido Stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.00,0:12:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There haven't been any \Ninjuries for a long time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.45,0:12:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that is the way Yuri does things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's controlling all dangerous \Nperformances by computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.25,0:12:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmmm, so that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.83,0:12:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But without any chance \Nto show off her skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.10,0:12:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand why Miss Layla doesn't \Nwant to come back to Kaleido Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.70,0:12:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.33,0:12:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But as an emergency doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a chance to \Nutilize my skills either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.20,0:12:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right now, I'm sure the \NMasked Star will show up today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.60,0:12:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty more minutes until the show starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.23,0:12:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until our life ends...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.54,0:12:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.50,0:12:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.54,0:12:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.79,0:12:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause unless the Masked Star \Nshows up, our show will end today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.08,0:12:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we will have the fate of paying \Nback the enormous forfeit fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.30,0:13:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, these kids want to get some autographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.31,0:13:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Autographs?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.79,0:13:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.02,0:13:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but the Masked Star has \Nsome business to take care of, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.51,0:13:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.16,0:13:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want an autograph from that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.02,0:13:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.75,0:13:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.73,0:13:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.22,0:13:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had so much fun. Right, brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.66,0:13:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw the show for the first \Ntime the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.08,0:13:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you guys came back here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Well, my brother didn't have \Nenough money for the admission fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.50,0:13:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he got an advance on his allowance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He begged Mom a lot, saying \Nthat he would pay her back
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.80,0:13:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by mowing the lawn for the next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Melissa, you don't have \Nto tell them all that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.75,0:13:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he paid for mine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.99,0:13:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm going to help him mow the lawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.29,0:13:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.45,0:13:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you help me, you'll end up \Nincreasing what I need to get done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:13:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a big girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.47,0:14:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do all kinds of stuff by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.04,0:14:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're looking forward to \Nseeing my show this much.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.91,0:14:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.12,0:14:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's show will be a lot \Nmore fun than the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.62,0:14:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a show worth more \Nthan a whole month of lawn mowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.00,0:14:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.69,0:14:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.86,0:14:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please have fun watching the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t believe you promised that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you'll end up disappointing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.35,0:14:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I won't. I'll never disappoint them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.79,0:14:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't allow myself to disappoint them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.73,0:14:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I think we have no choice \Nbut to do our best now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.16,0:14:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we don't have \Nthe Masked Star with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.25,0:14:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,let's make our show satisfying \Nfor the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.37,0:14:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we have to pay for the forfeit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why don't we let ourselves go and perform?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.75,0:14:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.54,0:15:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia, don't you have any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something we can prepare in \Nthe next fifteen minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.57,0:15:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I will come up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.95,0:15:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, each of us should try to think if \Nthere is anything we can do better than yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.68,0:15:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.87,0:15:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.95,0:15:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come up with something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.38,0:15:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.66,0:15:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it takes five seconds for each...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.70,0:15:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good! Maybe, we can do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.61,0:15:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ken, Marion, please help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.58,0:15:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.64,0:15:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can take care of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.33,0:15:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it starts soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.00,0:15:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see the...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.07,0:15:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already past the starting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're not telling \Nme that they took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.67,0:15:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.72,0:15:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here they go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.93,0:16:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.20,0:16:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.62,0:16:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.87,0:16:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! There!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.87,0:16:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.45,0:16:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Masked Star?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.54,0:16:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.56,0:16:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.70,0:16:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't miss that photo op.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.49,0:16:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.65,0:16:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.79,0:17:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go Melissa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.95,0:17:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says "Keep out"!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.41,0:17:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.18,0:17:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder if those kids are watching.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.72,0:17:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Masked Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.70,0:17:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Masked Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.66,0:17:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.00,0:17:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No matter what I think, there is \Nonly one person who can do this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.48,0:17:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That is... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.93,0:17:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be a big girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.19,0:17:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.84,0:18:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call a rescue team quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.20,0:18:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.41,0:18:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ladder is ready to fall off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.37,0:18:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.25,0:18:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know! I should use the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.11,0:18:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.04,0:18:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.74,0:18:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.99,0:18:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.41,0:18:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Masked Star is here. \NYou go first, Melissa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.25,0:18:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.20,0:18:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your big brother. So I will go next.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.91,0:18:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Melissa, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.45,0:18:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.74,0:19:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.06,0:19:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.08,0:19:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's going to crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.65,0:19:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.40,0:19:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.89,0:19:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I stay like this, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.03,0:19:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't know where I'm going to hit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.75,0:20:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.54,0:20:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.75,0:20:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.83,0:20:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The identity of the Masked \NStar is... as I thought...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.94,0:20:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't think of anybody \Nelse other than Miss Layla.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Elegant performance, strong movement...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.33,0:20:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're the same as Miss Layla. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This feeling traveling through me,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.25,0:20:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and everything else is \Nthe same as Miss Layla's.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.54,0:21:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I believe that the Masked Star is Miss Layla.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.45,0:21:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If Miss Layla is with us, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.05,0:21:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think creating our own \NKaleido Stage is possible.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.54,0:21:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not only that... I think \NI'm able to do anything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.26,0:21:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One day... without that mask,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.87,0:21:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hope we can appear on stage together again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.62,0:21:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One day... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.68,0:21:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Chariot...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.42,0:21:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The opportunity is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.55,0:21:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing left is going forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.25,0:21:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the show in the amusement \Npark is beating our show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.41,0:21:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our show is, like, showy \Nusing computers and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.26,0:21:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, like, it makes the show kinda fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.95,0:22:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, of course, it makes my job easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.80,0:22:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, of course, I don't need \Nto worry about injuries either.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.00,0:22:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.45,0:22:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's practice, practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.25,0:22:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this way, a brother and \Nsister were rescued safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.29,0:22:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later, both Sora Naegino and the Masked \NStar who performed after this incident
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.32,0:22:23.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Damned Masked Star...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.32,0:22:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,won applause from all the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.66,0:22:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.74,0:22:36.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Kaleido Star"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.33,0:22:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yuri, thank you for the flowers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.96,0:22:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And so, Freedom Lights' performance \Nis on the right track, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.79,0:22:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Yuri started meddling in \Nour business again, and...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.95,0:22:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It seems he's intent on \Ncompletely destroying us.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the mysterious Masked Star. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.96,0:22:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When the Masked Star's mask is removed,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.64,0:22:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the things reflected in her eyes are...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.39,0:22:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}are... are...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.00,0:22:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next time on Kaleido Star, "The \NAmazing Resolve Beneath the Mask."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.60,0:23:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My wings are my dream and \Non towards the sky...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.89,0:23:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Boku wa koko ni iru sora to \Nmichi no aida de mukai kaze{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.54,0:23:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Soshite mae o muiteiru mou nido \Nto kanashimi ga furanai youni to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.47,0:23:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ano kabe o koete kokomade kitanda{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.39,0:23:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nigedashitaku naru koto wa nando mo aru{\i0}
